<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Error 404 - Invalid URL</title>
    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            min-height: 100vh;
            background: linear-gradient(45deg, #ff6b6b, #556270, #4ecdc4);
            background-size: 400% 400%;
            animation: gradientBG 10s infinite alternate;
            color: #fff;
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            letter-spacing: 0.9px;
            word-spacing: 0.2rem;
            text-align: center;
        }

        @keyframes gradientBG {
            0% {
                background-position: 0% 50%;
            }
            100% {
                background-position: 100% 50%;
            }
        }

        .error-container {
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 3em;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        p {
            font-size: 1.2em;
            margin-bottom: 40px;
        }

        a {
            color: #fff;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: bold;
            border-bottom: 2px solid #fff;
        }

        a:hover {
            border-bottom: 2px solid #000;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

    <div class="error-container">
        <h1>Error 404 - Invalid URL</h1>
        <p>Oops! It looks like the page you are trying to access doesn't exist.</p>
        <p>Go back to <a href="/">home</a> or contact support.</p>
    </div>

</body>

</html>
